s able to enter the other's stories in new conceptual capacities. Dark Mirrors also examines the symmetrical patterns of early Jewish demonology that are often manifested in these fallen angels' imitation of the attributes of various heavenly beings, including principal angels and even God himself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Religious Studies. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Bible Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Studies / Exegesis & Hermeneutics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438439532423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438439532/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles